		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date><sic>sunday</sic></date> <placeName>Baltimore</placeName> <date>Decr 18<hi rend="underline">th</hi> 1835</date></p>
				<p>Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I should have <sic>aswered</sic> yours had I anything<lb/> of importance to write but as I wish you should hear from me<lb/> now and then&#44; I must say we are all well <sic>accept</sic> <persName>Mrs Depass</persName><lb/> has her old complains again last <date><sic>sunday</sic></date> <persName>Mr Tylor</persName> of <placeName>Richmond</placeName><lb/> my old <sic>neghbour</sic> paid us a visit he was on his way to <sic><placeName>philadelphia</placeName></sic><lb/> but the river being frozen&#44; he <sic>stopt</sic> here and returned to <placeName>Rich</placeName><lb/> on <date><sic>thursday</sic></date> he particularly inquired about you and desired to<lb/> be remembered to you&#44; he also related the fight of <persName>Myer</persName> &#38; <persName>Cohen</persName><lb/> that <persName>Mrs Cohen</persName> was the cause of it&#44; she is on <persName>Myer</persName> side&#44; <persName>Tylor</persName><lb/> also said that he believes it is owing on acct of <persName>Mrs Cohen</persName> to be<lb/> inclined to the christian church and <persName>Mr Cohen</persName> against it<lb/> well that is no doubt with me&#44; because when she was<lb/> here last year <add>&#63;</add> she went <add>Hebrew</add> night to the church&#44; and as<lb/> for the <add>&#63;</add> he is no better&#44; pray let me know how are all<lb/> my friends the <persName>Peixottos</persName> <sic>familia</sic> and how do you feel this cold<lb/> winter&#44; I would advise you to have a pair of woolen <sic>sogs</sic>&#44; put<lb/> over your shoes when you write to your Brother &#38; sister give my<lb/> love to them&#44; how is <persName>Mrs Hart</persName>&#44; do you go to <persName>Mr L Philips</persName> if so<lb/> remember me to him &#38; her.  I am getting <sic>Quite</sic> a prudent man<lb/> last night&#44; I was at <persName>Ben Cohen</persName> and did not stay later than one a clock<lb/> if I could think of any thing to add I would do so as I cannot<lb/> I remain your friend &#38; &#38; <persName role="author">Zalma Rehine</persName></p>
				<p>your Aunt <persName>Mr Depass</persName> <persName>Abby David</persName> send <sic>there</sic> love to you remember me<lb/> kindly to <persName>Mr &#38; Mrs Peixotto</persName> <persName>Simah</persName> <persName>Rachel</persName> <persName>Betty</persName> and the young gentlemen<lb/> and all my friends</p>
				<p><persName>Mrs Etting</persName> has been very unwell&#44; but is <sic>Quite</sic> better they send <sic>there</sic><lb/> respects to you&#44; <persName>Mr E Cohen</persName> is gone to <placeName>Charlestown</placeName> and will not be back<lb/> till the <sic>midle</sic> of <date>January</date> <persName>Mrs Cohen</persName> <sic>Desires</sic> to be remembered to you<lb/> if you see <persName>Miss Frances Chamberlain</persName> give our respects to her<lb/> we heard that <persName>Mrs Zeporo Seixas</persName> was <sic>wery</sic> sick&#44; have you heard<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> if so let us know <add>&#63;</add></p>
				<p rend="The page seems to have a portion cut off at the bottom."></p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
				<p><addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
				<p>to the Care of <persName>A. C Peixotto Esqr</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p>single</p>
